    "instructions": "Perform the following mathematical tasks:\n1. Derive the general scaling exponent for a dissipative PDE of the form $\\partial_t u + (u \\cdot \\nabla) u + (-\\Delta)^s u = 0$ (or similar nonlinear structure) in dimension $n$ with diffusion order $s$. Use dimensional analysis/scaling arguments to find the critical exponent (often related to the $L^p$ or Sobolev space scaling).\n2. For the following cases, identify $n$ and $s$ and calculate the exponent:\n   - 3D Navier-Stokes ($n=3, s=1$)\n   - 2D Navier-Stokes ($n=2, s=1$)\n   - 1D Burgers ($n=1, s=1$)\n   - SQG (Surface Quasi-Geostrophic) (provide values for critical and subcritical cases)\n   - MHD (Magnetohydrodynamics) (identify $n$ and $s$ for the standard dissipative case)\n   - Fractional Navier-Stokes (general $s$)\n3. Present the results in a clear verification table including columns for PDE Name, Dimension (n), Diffusion Order (s), and the Calculated Exponent.",
